SIMPLE: periscope
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Periscope
<hw>Per"i*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>peri-</ets> + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <def>A general or
comprehensive view.</def> <mark>[archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An optical instrument of tubular shape containing an
arrangement of lenses and mirrors (or prisms), allowing a person to
observe a field of view otherwise obstructed, as beyond an obstructing
object or (as in submarines) above the surface of the water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Periscopic</ent>⟦br⟧
